		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>PPMCK question</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The most current version of PPMCK has bankswitching galore for individual channels, but is the same possible for effects macros? It seems like it doesn't take much to get a $1FFF overflow message if (for instance) you have pitch macros which last hundreds of frames.
<br />
<br />Is there any kind of workaround, or is it simply a driver limitation?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>ionustron</b> [ Sun Feb 12, 2012 5:48 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I ran into a similar issue on an experiment in the summer.
<br />
<br />Very long envelopes will eventually begin pulling data from the next (I assume) designated area of data whether there's things you put there or not. I found that putting a smaller envelope between 2 huge ones alleviated this.
<br />
<br />However I don't recall if I actually ran into the overflow compile error on definitions. Unless you're trying to transcribe MANY passages of music for multiple channels I assume?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


